.TH R2MCP 1 "July 2026" "r2mcp" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
r2mcp \- Model Context Protocol server for radare2
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B r2mcp
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B r2mcp
serves radare2 tools over standard input/output or HTTP.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "-H " [ address : ] port
Start the HTTP MCP server. A bare port binds to
.B 127.0.0.1
only. To expose the server on all IPv4 interfaces, explicitly use
.BR -H " 0.0.0.0:" port .
Public listeners should use
.B -a
or
.B -A
to require Bearer authentication.
.TP
.BI "-a " token
Require HTTP Bearer authentication using
.IR token .
.TP
.B -A
Generate and require a random HTTP Bearer authentication token.
.TP
.BI "-S " url
Send tool calls to the supervisor control service at
.IR url .
.TP
.B -h
Show command help.
.TP
.B -v
Show the version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start a local-only server:
.EX
r2mcp -H 8765
.EE
.TP
Start a publicly reachable server with a generated token:
.EX
r2mcp -H 0.0.0.0:8765 -A
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR r2 (1)
